  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, design and positioning, would be harmful to the character and appearance of the locally listed host building; surrounding townscape and South Shoreditch Conservation Area, of which it forms part.&amp;nbsp; As such, the proposal is contrary policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity Through the Design-Led Approach), D4 (Delivering Good Design), (D8 Public Realm) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, design, positioning and method of illumination, would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on public safety of highway users by way of driver distraction. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity Through the Design-Led Approach), D4 (Delivering Good Design) and D8 (Public Realm) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).</span></p>",
    "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, design, positioning and method of illumination, would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on the amenity of the neighbouring occupiers by way of light pollution. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity Through the Design-Led Approach), D4 (Delivering Good Design) and D8 (Public Realm) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).</span></p>"
  ],
